ndle` is called from `reconcileIstioCSRDeployment` in the install file, which means I need to trace through how this function fits into the broader reconciliation flow. Completing the annotation update to stamp the hash onto the deployment, which mirrors how trustmanager handles it. For the make targets, I should include `make test` to run unit tests and `make build` to verify compilation. Now I'm reviewing the `deploymentSpecModified` function to see what deployment spec fields it currently compares—replicas, selector labels, template labels, container count, and the first container's properties like args, name, and image. The `ObjectMetadataModified` check at the end of `hasObjectChanged` handles label and annotation changes on the object itself, so there might be some existing gaps in what gets compared, but that's not something I need to worry about. For this task, I just need to add pod template annotation comparison to catch the hash change, which I'll insert right after the template labels check.\n\nNow I'm finalizing the implementation. Looking at the trustmanager pattern in configmaps.go, the function returns an empty string with nil on success when disabled, an empty string with an error on failure, and the hash with nil on success.\n\nFor istiocsr, I should follow the same pattern: return empty string with nil when the ConfigMap doesn't exist (graceful degradation), empty string with error on other failures, and the hash with nil on success. When the hash is empty, `updateCABundleHashAnnotation` should skip adding an annotation.\n\nI also need to update the test file since `createOrApplyDeployments` now has a different signature—all the existing test calls need the hash parameter added, and I should write tests for `computeCABundleHash` as well.\n\nI'll use the annotation key `cert-manager.io/ca-bundle-hash` as referenced in the AGENTS.md troubleshooting section, and I need to add an annotations check to `deploymentSpecModified` to detect when the CA bundle hash changes. I'm deciding whether to add the annotations check as a separate condition or combine it with the existing labels check. Looking at how trustmanager structures its `deploymentModified` function, it groups labels and annotations together, so I should probably follow that same pattern for consistency. I'm realizing the key difference between `reflect.DeepEqual` and `maps.Equal` when comparing nil maps to empty maps—they handle these edge cases differently. Since the fetched deployment might have nil annotations while the desired one has a populated map, I need to pick the comparison method that correctly detects this as a change. `reflect.DeepEqual` would catch this mismatch, which is what I want for detecting when annotations need to be updated. we want to update to remove the stale annotation. I'm considering using `maps.Equal` instead since it's cleaner and handles the nil vs empty map distinction well - both are treated as equivalent from Kubernetes' perspective, which is the right behavior here.\n\nLet me trace through the `install_istiocsr.go` flow to see where I need to add the CA bundle read.\n\nI'll place it right before the deployments step, reading and hashing the trusted CA bundle, then passing that hash into the deployment creation so the annotations get set correctly. Writing the implementation...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":9157,"cache_read_input_tokens":96685,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":9157,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":9},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"487683f8-2c8e-4318-84e5-a2bf0557341e","uuid":"a73e9343-e484-457a-b22a-cab3bbd98f66","timestamp":"2026-07-20T17:00:49.377Z","request_id":"req_vrtx_011CdDfUXyytKjXCmTtdTLcA"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_vrtx_01WbyGcX36XeyKM2eiwywJ1P","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have a thorough understanding of the codebase. Let me produce the complete implementation.\n\n---\n\n## Implementation: Content-Hash-Triggered Rolling Restart for IstioCSR\n\n### Summary of changes\n\nThe pattern mirrors trustmanager's `configmaps.go` → `deployments.go` flow:\n1. Read the CNO-injected CA bundle ConfigMap from the operator namespace\n2. SHA-256 hash the PEM content (not `resourceVersion`)\n3. Stamp the hash as a pod template annotation on the IstioCSR Deployment\n4. The existing `hasObjectChanged` check (with a new annotations comparison in `deploymentSpecModified`) acts as the idempotency guard — skipping the update when the hash is unchanged\n\n---\n\n### File 1: NEW — `pkg/controller/istiocsr/configmaps.go`\n\n```go\npackage istiocsr\n\nimport (\n\t\"crypto/sha256\"\n\t\"encoding/hex\"\n\t\"fmt\"\n\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n\t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"\n\n\t\"github.com/openshift/cert-manager-operator/api/operator/v1alpha1\"\n\t\"github.com/openshift/cert-manager-operator/pkg/controller/common\"\n)\n\n// readAndHashTrustedCABundle reads the CNO-injected CA bundle ConfigMap from the\n// operator namespace, computes a SHA-256 hash of the PEM data, and adds a watch\n// label so that changes to the ConfigMap trigger reconciliation.\n// Returns (\"\", nil) when the ConfigMap does not exist (graceful degradation for\n// non-OpenShift clusters).\nfunc (r *Reconciler) readAndHashTrustedCABundle(istiocsr *v1alpha1.IstioCSR) (string, error) {\n\tcm := &corev1.ConfigMap{}\n\tkey := client.ObjectKey{\n\t\tNamespace: common.OperatorNamespace,\n\t\tName:      common.TrustedCABundleConfigMapName,\n\t}\n\tif err := r.Get(r.ctx, key, cm); err != nil {\n\t\tif errors.IsNotFound(err) {\n\t\t\tr.log.V(4).Info(\"CNO-injected CA bundle ConfigMap not found, skipping hash annotation\",\n\t\t\t\t\"configmap\", common.TrustedCABundleConfigMapName,\n\t\t\t\t\"namespace\", common.OperatorNamespace)\n\t\t\treturn \"\", nil\n\t\t}\n\t\treturn \"\", common.FromClientError(\n\t\t\terr,\n\t\t\t\"failed to read CA bundle ConfigMap %q in namespace %q\",\n\t\t\tcommon.TrustedCABundleConfigMapName, common.OperatorNamespace,\n\t\t)\n\t}\n\n\tcaBundle, ok := cm.Data[common.TrustedCABundleKey]\n\tif !ok || caBundle == \"\" {\n\t\treturn \"\", fmt.Errorf(\"CA bundle ConfigMap %q does not contain key %q\",\n\t\t\tcommon.TrustedCABundleConfigMapName, common.TrustedCABundleKey)\n\t}\n\n\tif err := r.updateWatchLabel(cm, istiocsr); err != nil {\n\t\treturn \"\", common.FromClientError(err,\n\t\t\t\"failed to update watch label on CA bundle ConfigMap %s/%s\",\n\t\t\tcommon.OperatorNamespace, common.TrustedCABundleConfigMapName)\n\t}\n\n\treturn computeCABundleHash(caBundle), nil\n}\n\n// computeCABundleHash returns the SHA-256 hash of the CA bundle PEM content.\n// The hash covers PEM content, not resourceVersion, so rolling restarts happen\n// only when the actual certificate content changes.\nfunc computeCABundleHash(caBundle string) string {\n\thash := sha256.Sum256([]byte(caBundle))\n\treturn hex.EncodeToString(hash[:])\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### File 2: NEW — `pkg/controller/istiocsr/configmaps_test.go`\n\n```go\npackage istiocsr\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\t\"crypto/sha256\"\n\t\"encoding/hex\"\n\t\"testing\"\n\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n\tapierrors \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n\tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n\t\"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/types\"\n\n\t\"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"\n\n\t\"github.com/openshift/cert-manager-operator/pkg/controller/common\"\n\t\"github.com/openshift/cert-manager-operator/pkg/controller/common/fakes\"\n)\n\nfunc TestComputeCABundleHash(t *testing.T) {\n\tpem := \"-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----\\nMIIBfoo\\n-----END CERTIFICATE-----\\n\"\n\tgot := computeCABundleHash(pem)\n\n\traw := sha256.Sum256([]byte(pem))\n\twant := hex.EncodeToString(raw[:])\n\tif got != want {\n\t\tt.Errorf(\"computeCABundleHash() = %q, want %q\", got, want)\n\t}\n\n\tif computeCABundleHash(pem) != computeCABundleHash(pem) {\n\t\tt.Error(\"computeCABundleHash() is not deterministic\")\n\t}\n\n\tif computeCABundleHash(\"a\") == computeCABundleHash(\"b\") {\n\t\tt.Error(\"computeCABundleHash() returned same hash for different input\")\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc TestReadAndHashTrustedCABundle(t *testing.T) {\n\ttests := []struct {\n\t\tname    string\n\t\tpreReq  func(*fakes.FakeCtrlClient)\n\t\twantErr string\n\t\twantLen int\n\t}{\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"returns hash when ConfigMap exists\",\n\t\t\tpreReq: func(m *fakes.FakeCtrlClient) {\n\t\t\t\tm.GetCalls(func(ctx context.Context, key types.NamespacedName, obj client.Object) error {\n\t\t\t\t\tif cm, ok := obj.(*corev1.ConfigMap); ok &&\n\t\t\t\t\t\tkey.Name == common.TrustedCABundleConfigMapName &&\n\t\t\t\t\t\tkey.Namespace == common.OperatorNamespace {\n\t\t\t\t\t\tcm.ObjectMeta = metav1.ObjectMeta{\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tName:      common.TrustedCABundleConfigMapName,\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tNamespace: common.OperatorNamespace,\n\t\t\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\t\t\tcm.Data = map[string]string{\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tcommon.TrustedCABundleKey: \"-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----\\ntest\\n-----END CERTIFICATE-----\\n\",\n\t\t\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\t\treturn nil\n\t\t\t\t})\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\twantLen: 64, // SHA-256 hex length\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"returns empty when ConfigMap not found\",\n\t\t\tpreReq: func(m *fakes.FakeCtrlClient) {\n\t\t\t\tm.GetCalls(func(ctx context.Context, key types.NamespacedName, obj client.Object) error {\n\t\t\t\t\tif key.Name == common.TrustedCABundleConfigMapName {\n\t\t\t\t\t\treturn apierrors.NewNotFound(corev1.Resource(\"configmaps\"), common.TrustedCABundleConfigMapName)\n\t\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\t\treturn nil\n\t\t\t\t})\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\twantLen: 0,\n\t\t},\n\t\t{\n\t\t\tname: \"returns error when key is missing\",\n\t\t\tpreReq: func(m *fakes.FakeCtrlClient) {\n\t\t\t\tm.GetCalls(func(ctx context.Context, key types.NamespacedName, obj client.Object) error {\n\t\t\t\t\tif cm, ok := obj.(*corev1.ConfigMap); ok &&\n\t\t\t\t\t\tkey.Name == common.TrustedCABundleConfigMapName {\n\t\t\t\t\t\tcm.Data = map[string]string{}\n\t\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\t\treturn nil\n\t\t\t\t})\n\t\t\t},\n\t\t\twantErr: \"does not contain key\",\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\tfor _, tt := range tests {\n\t\tt.Run(tt.name, func(t *testing.T) {\n\t\t\tr := testReconciler(t)\n\t\t\tmock := &fakes.FakeCtrlClient{}\n\t\t\tif tt.preReq != nil {\n\t\t\t\ttt.preReq(mock)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tr.CtrlClient = mock\n\t\t\tistiocsr := testIstioCSR()\n\n\t\t\thash, err := r.readAndHashTrustedCABundle(istiocsr)\n\t\t\tif tt.wantErr != \"\" {\n\t\t\t\tif err == nil || !contains(err.Error(), tt.wantErr) {\n\t\t\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"readAndHashTrustedCABundle() err = %v, want containing %q\", err, tt.wantErr)\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t\treturn\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\tt.Fatalf(\"readAndHashTrustedCABundle() unexpected err: %v\", err)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif len(hash) != tt.wantLen {\n\t\t\t\tt.Errorf(\"readAndHashTrustedCABundle() hash length = %d, want %d\", len(hash), tt.wantLen)\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t})\n\t}\n}\n\nfunc contains(s, substr string) bool {\n\treturn len(s) >= len(substr) && (s == substr || len(s) > 0 && containsSubstring(s, substr))\n}\n\nfunc containsSubstring(s, substr string) bool {\n\tfor i := 0; i <= len(s)-len(substr); i++ {\n\t\tif s[i:i+len(substr)] == substr {\n\t\t\treturn true\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn false\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### File 3: MODIFY — `pkg/controller/istiocsr/constants.go`\n\nAdd the annotation constant inside the first `const` block, after the `istiocsrResourceWatchLabelValueFmt` constant:\n\n```go\n// caBundleHashAnnotation is the pod template annotation that tracks the\n// SHA-256 hash of the CNO-injected CA bundle PEM content. Changes to this\n// annotation trigger a rolling restart of the IstioCSR pods.\ncaBundleHashAnnotation = \"cert-manager.io/ca-bundle-hash\"\n```\n\n**Exact diff** — in `constants.go`, after line 81 (`istiocsrResourceWatchLabelValueFmt = \"%s_%s\"`), add:\n\n```diff\n \t// istiocsrResourceWatchLabelName is the value format assigned to istiocsrResourceWatchLabelName label, which\n \t// will be of the form <istiocsr_namespace>/<istiocsr_instance-Name>.\n \tistiocsrResourceWatchLabelValueFmt = \"%s_%s\"\n+\n+\t// caBundleHashAnnotation is the pod template annotation that tracks the\n+\t// SHA-256 hash of the CNO-injected CA bundle PEM content.\n+\tcaBundleHashAnnotation = \"cert-manager.io/ca-bundle-hash\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### File 4: MODIFY — `pkg/controller/istiocsr/deployments.go`\n\n**Change 1** — `createOrApplyDeployments` signature (line 31):\n\n```diff\n-func (r *Reconciler) createOrApplyDeployments(istiocsr *v1alpha1.IstioCSR, resourceLabels map[string]string, istioCSRCreateRecon bool) error {\n-\tdesired, err := r.getDeploymentObject(istiocsr, resourceLabels)\n+func (r *Reconciler) createOrApplyDeployments(istiocsr *v1alpha1.IstioCSR, resourceLabels map[string]string, istioCSRCreateRecon bool, caBundleHash string) error {\n+\tdesired, err := r.getDeploymentObject(istiocsr, resourceLabels, caBundleHash)\n```\n\n**Change 2** — `getDeploymentObject` signature and body (line 73):\n\n```diff\n-func (r *Reconciler) getDeploymentObject(istiocsr *v1alpha1.IstioCSR, resourceLabels map[string]string) (*appsv1.Deployment, error) {\n+func (r *Reconciler) getDeploymentObject(istiocsr *v1alpha1.IstioCSR, resourceLabels map[string]string, caBundleHash string) (*appsv1.Deployment, error) {\n```\n\nAnd at the end of `getDeploymentObject`, just before `return deployment, nil` (after line 103's `updateVolumes` call), add:\n\n```diff\n \tif err := r.updateVolumes(deployment, istiocsr, resourceLabels); err != nil {\n \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to update volume %s/%s: %w\", istiocsr.GetNamespace(), istiocsr.GetName(), err)\n \t}\n \n+\tupdateCABundleHashAnnotation(deployment, caBundleHash)\n+\n \treturn deployment, nil\n }\n```\n\n**Change 3** — Add the new function after `updatePodTemplateLabels` (after line 135):\n\n```go\n// updateCABundleHashAnnotation stamps the SHA-256 hash of the CNO-injected CA\n// bundle as a pod template annotation. When the hash changes, Kubernetes treats\n// it as a pod template change and triggers a rolling restart.\nfunc updateCABundleHashAnnotation(deployment *appsv1.Deployment, caBundleHash string) {\n\tif caBundleHash == \"\" {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\tif deployment.Spec.Template.Annotations == nil {\n\t\tdeployment.Spec.Template.Annotations = make(map[string]string)\n\t}\n\tdeployment.Spec.Template.Annotations[caBundleHashAnnotation] = caBundleHash\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### File 5: MODIFY — `pkg/controller/istiocsr/install_istiocsr.go`\n\n**Change** — In `reconcileIstioCSRDeployment`, before the `createOrApplyDeployments` call (before line 49), add the CA bundle read and pass the hash:\n\n```diff\n \tif err := r.createOrApplyCertificates(istiocsr, resourceLabels, istioCSRCreateRecon); err != nil {\n \t\tr.log.Error(err, \"failed to reconcile certificate resource\")\n \t\treturn err\n \t}\n \n-\tif err := r.createOrApplyDeployments(istiocsr, resourceLabels, istioCSRCreateRecon); err != nil {\n+\tcaBundleHash, err := r.readAndHashTrustedCABundle(istiocsr)\n+\tif err != nil {\n+\t\tr.log.Error(err, \"failed to read and hash trusted CA bundle\")\n+\t\treturn err\n+\t}\n+\n+\tif err := r.createOrApplyDeployments(istiocsr, resourceLabels, istioCSRCreateRecon, caBundleHash); err != nil {\n \t\tr.log.Error(err, \"failed to reconcile deployment resource\")\n \t\treturn err\n \t}\n```\n\nThe full `import` block stays unchanged since `fmt` and the operator packages are already imported.\n\n---\n\n### File 6: MODIFY — `pkg/controller/istiocsr/utils.go`\n\n**Change** — In `deploymentSpecModified` (line 308), add pod template annotations comparison. After the template labels check (